                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18760626-name-212" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18760626-name-212" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18760626-name-212" type="surname" value="DOWN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18760626-name-212" type="given" value="EVA CROMPTON"></interp>EVA CROMPTON DOWN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>). This is my signature to one of these bills, and the other is Hilton's—I have a receipt at home similar to this signed by Charles. (<hi rend="italic">This was a receipt for</hi> 42<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. <hi rend="italic">by the witness and her brother Charles, to which they would have a right at Mrs. Down's death, being a reversion under the will of the late Colonel Hutchinson</hi>.)</p>
